{
  "texts": [
    "In each sector we indicate the number of independent gauge-invariant structures (GIS), the number of independent operators in the exact U(2) 5 limit, and the tables where we report current bounds on the corresponding WCs.",
    "JHEP03(2024)049In fact, choosing the flavor basis where the Y † f Y f matrices are diagonal (f = u, d, e), we can identify the right-handed third-generation fields as those associated to the largest eigenvalues.",
    "Neglecting neutrino masses, a similar non-ambiguous choice is possible also for the lepton doublets, since we can choose a flavor basis where Y † e Y e and Y e Y † e are both diagonal.",
    "The only non-trivial case is related to the quark doublets, given the misalignment implied by the Cabibbo-Kobayashi-Maskawa (CKM) matrix (V CKM).",
    "Denoting as q (u) ≡ {q u, q c, q t } and q (d) ≡ {q d, q s, q b } the doublets in the up-and down-quark mass-eigenstate basis, respectively, we define the U(2) q singlet field asq 3 = (1 -ε F)δ 3r + ε F V 3r q (d) r ≈ q b + ε F (V ts q s + V td q d) (2.5) = (1 -ε F)(V †) 3r + ε F δ 3r q (u) r ≈ q t + (1 -ε F)(V * cb q c + V * ub q u)."
  ]
